19/01/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- In a joint operation, police and organised crime control units broke up an arms ring Saturday (17 January). 
Officers detained five men, including a former employee of the Arsenal arms producing company in Kazanluk. 
The men were charged with converting gas pistols into combat ones and selling them. 
This was the third major operation targeting illegal arms production and trade over the past month. 
(BNT, BTA, BNR - 17/01/04)
